I try to write a poem on the bike ride from your house
--
My Sailor Friend
--
—something about cicadas, minimally-applied sunscreen, the teachings of your friends, the garden many/Mary must've sat in and felt so much grief, really hot sleepovers scaring off night terrors and so so many dinners, about 30-minute bike rides and—

—something about trying to make a poem from disparate events and, being unable to, ending up—